      <relatedmaterial>
         <head id="a5">RELATED MATERIALS</head>
         <p>The "Stacewicz, Richard VVAW interviews, 1992-1995" at the Wisconsin Historical Society contain a
            tape-recorded interview with Sheldon conducted by Richard Stacewicz in preparation for
            his book, "Winter Soldiers: An Oral History of the Vietnam Veterans Against the War"
            (1997). State Historical Society of Wisconsin, Archives Division, 816 State Street, Madison, Wis. 53706.</p>
         <p>Related collection: Ramsdell, Sheldon Papers, (#1996-28). Files of his AIDS activism
            during his 12 years living in San Francisco are at the GLBT Historical Society, 657
            Mission Street #300, San Francisco, CA 94105 Phone: 415.777.5455. Email:
            info@glbthistory.org</p>
        
      </relatedmaterial>
      <odd type="notes">
         <head id="a6">NOTES</head>
         <p>Collecting Program: Human Sexuality Collection.</p>
      </odd>
